value.0: A quiet woman, pouring over the same children's fairy tail she's been reading for the last year or so. She refuses to participate in anything aside from dinner time and "lights out". Her hair is, curiously, white - despite looking rather young. There are some superstitions that say your tresses can turn this color after an episode of intense grief or shock.
A book in the hand is worth two on the shelf!

This patient is concentrating on a rather detailed painting of a bowl of fruit. Her delicate hand trembles at the slightest distraction, which flusters her to no end. The nurses caution that you leave her be.

You step into a dark, dismal room; despite the optimism and light spread by the Salandran clergy, one can't help but to feel an overwhelmingly dark feeling will inside. The walls and floors and padded by a soft, unassuming material that would be safe for even the most fragile of flowers to frolick in. There is nary a window or even an object to distract one's self from the dizzying amount of white on white on white.
